wifi: mt76: compat: adapt to flattened ieee80211_mgmt action layout (kernel 7.1)

Kernel 7.1 reworked struct ieee80211_mgmt: the per-action union (formerly
mgmt->u.action.u) was flattened and the common 'category'/'action_code'
bytes were hoisted out of it, while IEEE80211_MIN_ACTION_SIZE turned from a
plain constant into the function-like macro IEEE80211_MIN_ACTION_SIZE(type)
== offsetofend(struct ieee80211_mgmt, u.action.type).

This DKMS package extracts mt76 from the kernel 7.0 tarball (old layout) but
is built against the host kernel. On 7.1+ the build fails with:

  error: 'IEEE80211_MIN_ACTION_SIZE' undeclared
  error: 'struct <anonymous>' has no member named 'u'

Guard the ADDBA action parsing on LINUX_VERSION_CODE so the new accessors
are used on >= 7.1 while the old layout is kept for the supported 6.17..7.0
hosts. IEEE80211_MIN_ACTION_SIZE(addba_req)/(action_code) cover exactly the
fields read (capab / action_code), matching the in-tree mt76 conversion.

Signed-off-by: bentoo overlay

--- a/mt76_connac_mac.c
+++ b/mt76_connac_mac.c
@@ -1,6 +1,7 @@
 // SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause-Clear
 /* Copyright (C) 2020 MediaTek Inc. */
 
+#include <linux/version.h>
 #include "mt76_connac.h"
 #include "mt76_connac2_mac.h"
 #include "dma.h"
@@ -413,10 +414,17 @@
 	u32 val;
 
 	if (ieee80211_is_action(fc) &&
+#if LINUX_VERSION_CODE >= KERNEL_VERSION(7, 1, 0)
+	    skb->len >= IEEE80211_MIN_ACTION_SIZE(addba_req) &&
+	    mgmt->u.action.category == WLAN_CATEGORY_BACK &&
+	    mgmt->u.action.action_code == WLAN_ACTION_ADDBA_REQ) {
+		u16 capab = le16_to_cpu(mgmt->u.action.addba_req.capab);
+#else
 	    skb->len >= IEEE80211_MIN_ACTION_SIZE + 1 + 1 + 2 &&
 	    mgmt->u.action.category == WLAN_CATEGORY_BACK &&
 	    mgmt->u.action.u.addba_req.action_code == WLAN_ACTION_ADDBA_REQ) {
 		u16 capab = le16_to_cpu(mgmt->u.action.u.addba_req.capab);
+#endif
 
 		txwi[5] |= cpu_to_le32(MT_TXD5_ADD_BA);
 		tid = (capab >> 2) & IEEE80211_QOS_CTL_TID_MASK;
